article.headline: Texas-Pan American 88, Alcorn St. 74
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- Zach Trader scored 18 points and all five Texas-Pan American starters scored in double figures Saturday in an 88-74 win over Alcorn State in the consolation game of the GranTree Classic at Montana State University. Nathan Hawkins had 17 points and six rebounds, while Brian Burrell added 16 points for the Broncs (5-3). Burrell was 6-of-9 from the field. Texas-Pan American took an early 15-4 lead and went into halftime ahead 44-31. The Broncs took their biggest lead, 76-61, with 7:44 remaining. Alex Owumi led the Braves (0-6) with 20 points.
